尽管取得了这些进展，但有证据表明许多女性仍然无法实现她们的目标。
女性和男性之间的收入差距虽然比几年前有所缩小，但仍然很大；
Despite this progress, evidence suggests that many women remain unable to achieve their goals.
The gap in earnings between women and men, although smaller than it was years ago, is still significant; 

妇女在某些行业和职业中的代表性仍然不足；
太多的女性努力兼顾工作和家庭的愿望。
women continue to be underrepresented in certain industries and occupations; 
and too many women struggle to combine aspirations for work and family.

平等机会和工作场所规则和规范的障碍阻碍了进一步的进步
无法支持合理的工作与生活平衡。

Further advancement has been hampered by barriers to equal opportunity and workplace rules and norms that 
fail to support a reasonable work-life balance.


